---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '@components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '@components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Daydream Retriever — Support"
  description="Support and FAQs for Daydream Retriever, a hand-painted one-tap arcade flyer from Northland Studios."
>
  <Nav />

  <main id="main">
    <header class="page-hero">
      <div class="page-hero-inner">
        <div class="mono label">§ Daydream Retriever</div>
        <h1>Support</h1>
        <p class="lede">A dreamy flap through the soft-edged sky. iPhone + iPad. One tap, hand-painted, no ads, no tracking.</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="section narrow">
      <div class="mono label">§ Quick links</div>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/apps/daydream-retriever/privacy">Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://dd-1600.github.io">Northland Studios &rarr;</a></li>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:danieldavis16@gmail.com">danieldavis16@gmail.com</a></li>
      </ul>

      <p>Found a bug? Have a question? Email us — every message is read and usually answered within 48 hours.</p>

      <div class="mono label">§ FAQ</div>

      <h3>How do I play?</h3>
      <p>Tap anywhere on screen to flap. Avoid the obstacles, collect the floaty bits, ride the soft-edged sky as long as you can. There's no second control to learn.</p>

      <h3>Can I play offline?</h3>
      <p>Yes. Daydream Retriever is fully playable offline. No network connection is required for the game itself, cosmetic unlocks, daily runs, or local high scores. The only things that need a network are the optional tip jar and iCloud sync.</p>

      <h3>How do I restore my purchases?</h3>
      <p>Open <em>Settings</em> inside the app and tap <strong>Restore Purchases</strong>. StoreKit will re-grant any tip-jar entitlements tied to your Apple ID. There are no consumables, so a single restore covers everything.</p>

      <h3>Why won't the tip jar work?</h3>
      <p>A few common causes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Sandbox / TestFlight build:</strong> if you're on a TestFlight build, you'll be hitting Apple's StoreKit sandbox, which sometimes rejects purchases or runs slowly. Production App Store builds use real StoreKit and are reliable.</li>
        <li><strong>iCloud not signed in:</strong> StoreKit needs an Apple ID. <em>Settings &rarr; [your name]</em> on iOS — make sure you're signed in.</li>
        <li><strong>Restrictions:</strong> if Screen Time has <em>In-App Purchases</em> set to <em>Don't Allow</em>, the tip jar will refuse to load. <em>Settings &rarr; Screen Time &rarr; Content &amp; Privacy Restrictions &rarr; iTunes &amp; App Store Purchases</em>.</li>
        <li><strong>Still stuck?</strong> Email us with the error message and your iOS version.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Does my progress sync between iPhone and iPad?</h3>
      <p>Yes, automatically, as long as both devices are signed in to the same iCloud account. Game state syncs via Apple's private key-value store. There's no Northland account to create.</p>

      <h3>How do I delete my data?</h3>
      <p>Uninstall the app. All local data is on-device. For iCloud-synced state: <em>Settings &rarr; Apple ID &rarr; iCloud &rarr; Manage Account Storage &rarr; Daydream Retriever &rarr; Delete Data</em>.</p>

      <h3>How do I report a bug or request a feature?</h3>
      <p>Email <a href="mailto:danieldavis16@gmail.com">danieldavis16@gmail.com</a> with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your iOS version (<em>Settings &rarr; General &rarr; About &rarr; iOS Version</em>)</li>
        <li>Your device model</li>
        <li>Steps to reproduce, if a bug</li>
        <li>A screenshot if it helps</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Is there a Mac / web / Android version?</h3>
      <p>Not currently. v1.0 is iPhone + iPad only.</p>

      <div class="mono label">§ Known issues</div>
      <p>None currently. This section will be updated per release as real-user reports come in.</p>

      <div class="mono label">§ Contact</div>
      <p>
        <a href="mailto:danieldavis16@gmail.com">danieldavis16@gmail.com</a> — usually replies within 48 hours, often same day.
      </p>

      <p class="back">
        <em>Daydream Retriever is made by Northland Studios.</em>
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero { background: var(--bg-soft); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .page-hero-inner { max-width: var(--col-narrow); margin: 0 auto; padding: clamp(60px, 10vh, 100px) var(--pad-page); }
  .page-hero .label { color: var(--accent); margin: 0 0 14px 0; }
  .page-hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 56px);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.012em;
    margin: 0 0 22px 0;
  }
  .page-hero .lede {
    font-size: 19px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }

  .section.narrow { padding-top: clamp(50px, 6vh, 80px); padding-bottom: clamp(50px, 6vh, 80px); max-width: var(--col-narrow); margin: 0 auto; padding-left: var(--pad-page); padding-right: var(--pad-page); }
  .section .label { color: var(--accent); margin: 36px 0 12px 0; }
  .section .label:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .section p, .section ul {
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.66;
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
    margin: 0 0 18px 0;
    max-width: 62ch;
  }
  .section h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 19px;
    color: var(--ink-primary);
    margin: 22px 0 8px 0;
    max-width: 62ch;
  }
  .section ul { padding-left: 22px; }
  .section li { margin: 0 0 8px 0; }
  .section a { color: var(--accent); }
  .section .back { margin-top: 36px; color: var(--ink-muted); }
</style>
